{
  "id": "PLACE_the_vitrified_rift",
  "label": "The Vitrified Rift",
  "description": "The Vitrified Rift forms a narrow cave where Blackchisel Mountain’s iron-dark ribs split along a band of glassy seamstone left by the mountain’s ancient heat anomaly. Its walls bear fused slag, knife-bright fractures, and stunted stalactites hardened into black-green glaze that reflects lanternlight in broken facets. Chisel marks and old tally notches cut into the vitrified skin register regulated extraction and later attempts at erasure under competing charter claims. The floor drops in short steps into a cold draft, carrying grit and the metallic tang of exposed ore.",
